1
00:00:03,669 --> 00:00:07,777
Excellent. All right, enjoy.

2
00:00:07,777 --> 00:00:11,951
Could you ever see automating the decorating of these donuts?

3
00:00:11,951 --> 00:00:18,568
We find that the best way to drive efficiency is with the core-shell donut or the ring.

4
00:00:18,568 --> 00:00:28,609
But when it comes to putting the finishing touches on our donuts, that complexity requires the hands and the eye coordination of our Krispy Kremers.

5
00:00:28,609 --> 00:00:30,400
Plus a robot could squish them, right?

6
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,554
I would be very worried about squishing the donuts.

7
00:00:33,554 --> 00:00:38,812
After a period of missed sales targets and profit losses, Krispy Kreme is looking for ways to grow.

8
00:00:38,812 --> 00:00:42,797
That means pushing its donut-making machines to do more and more.

9
00:00:42,797 --> 00:00:45,401
But even here, automation has its limits.

10
00:00:45,401 --> 00:00:52,302
While machines can mix and glaze a standard donut, they still struggle with seasonal and limited-time designs.

11
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:59,864
We have piloted a couple of robot-style solutions to see if they would work, but it got super messy.

12
00:00:59,864 --> 00:01:02,501
The glaze got into the joints of the robots.

13
00:01:02,501 --> 00:01:13,273
It's pretty tough to not harm the quality of the donut, and that's the most important thing for us.

14
00:01:13,273 --> 00:01:15,752
Oh, look, there's the donuts.

15
00:01:15,752 --> 00:01:19,652
Yeah, this is one of our largest lines that we operate across the country.

16
00:01:19,652 --> 00:01:21,576
It can make 400 dozen donuts an hour.

17
00:01:21,576 --> 00:01:25,905
More than 50% of the donuts we sell are our original glaze.

18
00:01:25,905 --> 00:01:29,690
So it's absolutely critical that we get this process right.

19
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:32,151
How many unusable donuts do you tend to have?

20
00:01:32,151 --> 00:01:37,064
So what we do is, we try and aim for over 93% efficiency.

21
00:01:37,064 --> 00:01:41,656
We obviously do make sure that the donut has to be perfect.

22
00:01:41,656 --> 00:01:43,388
We really care about quality a lot.

23
00:01:43,388 --> 00:01:45,430
I just saw one got taken off.

24
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:48,213
It looked a little sad.

25
00:01:48,213 --> 00:01:51,172
It's really important that they retain the perfect shape.

26
00:01:51,172 --> 00:01:57,212
What would you say the biggest bottleneck is currently in these manufacturing facilities?

27
00:01:57,212 --> 00:02:03,839
Making sure that as we change flavors, we're setting the teams up for success.

28
00:02:03,839 --> 00:02:09,184
The fact that we still have that hand-decorated element allows us to be incredibly agile as a business.

29
00:02:09,184 --> 00:02:11,595
And offer a huge variety for our guests.

30
00:02:11,595 --> 00:02:13,374
But it is costly, right?

31
00:02:13,374 --> 00:02:18,383
It is costly, but it's definitely worth it.

32
00:02:18,383 --> 00:02:25,348
Krispy Kreme has more than 6,500 employees across the US, and about 10% to 15% of them work as decorators.&nbsp;

33
00:02:25,348 --> 00:02:29,269
Each can decorate up to 50 dozen donuts per hour.

34
00:02:29,269 --> 00:02:30,668
[和员工对话] What's the hardest part of your job?

35
00:02:30,668 --> 00:02:33,371
The hardest part, the demand.

36
00:02:33,371 --> 00:02:36,880
Yeah, it'd be the demand, 'cause sometimes you have a lot to make.

37
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:41,292
I see these ladies have, like, so many donuts they're making, but sometimes you have to have a whole lot.

38
00:02:41,292 --> 00:02:45,289
Depending on how popular the donut is, it really sells a whole lot.

39
00:02:45,289 --> 00:02:49,801
And part of that is because you have so many limited-time offers, right?

40
00:02:49,801 --> 00:02:53,630
Yes, yes. Limited-time offers and sales, they merge together and people are like, "Hey, donuts."

41
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:57,244
Do you think your job could be automated ever?

42
00:02:57,244 --> 00:02:58,742
Could it be automated?

43
00:02:58,742 --> 00:03:00,896
I mean, to an extent maybe.

44
00:03:00,896 --> 00:03:06,008
But all the different things that we do on top of the donut, I don't think a machine could do that.

45
00:03:06,008 --> 00:03:07,688
Doesn't do it with love.

46
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:09,842
There's no love in that.

47
00:03:09,842 --> 00:03:10,854
Robot can't do that.

48
00:03:10,854 --> 00:03:13,804
Not at all, I don't think so.

49
00:03:13,804 --> 00:03:17,074
[Narrator] But Krispy Kreme is under pressure to become more efficient.

50
00:03:17,074 --> 00:03:23,817
The company is still fighting to remain out of the red after its ambitious deal to sell donuts at McDonald's fell apart.

51
00:03:23,817 --> 00:03:25,561
[和Manager对话问答] Let's talk about McDonald's.

52
00:03:25,561 --> 00:03:27,313
What happened with that?

53
00:03:27,313 --> 00:03:40,446
I think that the consumer was really looking for more convenient access to Krispy Kreme's fresh donuts, and the partnership with McDonald's was designed to enable that, and certainly started effectively.

54
00:03:40,446 --> 00:03:49,456
However, we found that the revenue streams weren't necessarily sustainable over time because the conditions weren't as optimum as we have with many of our other customers.

55
00:03:49,456 --> 00:03:51,036
Let's get more into the nuts and bolts.

56
00:03:51,036 --> 00:03:54,683
I know you manufacture a lot of your own equipment.

57
00:03:54,683 --> 00:03:57,180
It's kind of unusual.

58
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:58,404
How precise are these machines?

59
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:03,966
Well, I mean, I think there is always an element of the human element to make sure they run well.

60
00:04:03,966 --> 00:04:10,702
But yeah, they can do, one of our lines, a standard line, does 200 dozen donuts an hour.

61
00:04:10,702 --> 00:04:13,321
We have ones that can do all the way up to 400 dozen.

62
00:04:13,321 --> 00:04:22,020
You do have to keep an eye on many of the temperatures and humidity, and making sure the yield of these machines is working effectively.

63
00:04:22,020 --> 00:04:26,999
I always think that our Krispy Kreme employees bring something special to our donuts.

64
00:04:26,999 --> 00:04:32,315
I do think that there's opportunity to improve and become more efficient.

65
00:04:32,315 --> 00:04:42,918
I do think we can leverage technology, and we're exploring various things, whether it's in the manufacturing process or in distribution, demand planning, supply planning, the like, where we can leverage technology.

66
00:04:42,918 --> 00:04:46,592
But I'm really proud of what our Krispy Kreme does too.

67
00:04:46,592 --> 00:04:49,113
Where would you say you are in your turnaround story right now?

68
00:04:49,113 --> 00:04:51,302
Yeah, we've been growing the brand.

69
00:04:51,302 --> 00:04:53,905
Krispy Kreme is a growth story for many years.

70
00:04:53,905 --> 00:05:05,995
We implemented a turnaround in the middle of last year because we wanted to make sure that growth was behind sustainable revenue streams, profitable, and that we strengthened our balance sheet.

71
00:05:05,995 --> 00:05:08,357
And you are forecasting a profitable year this year?

72
00:05:08,357 --> 00:05:13,143
We are, we're forecasting 2% to 4% system-wide sales growth.

73
00:05:13,143 --> 00:05:22,539
And to drive up margins as we have been, we've seen margins go up 250 basis points so far since we implemented the turnaround.

74
00:05:22,539 --> 00:05:37,645
We expect to continue to see that margin improvement, all as we shift to a more capital-like model, franchising becoming a bigger part of the revenue stream, so that we can continue to grow, but in a more capital-efficient way.

75
00:05:37,645 --> 00:05:43,507
What is the future for donuts in this kind of health-conscious GLP-1 era?

76
00:05:43,507 --> 00:05:53,317
What I think our customers are looking for when it comes to donuts is great quality, great tasting, fresh donuts, and that's what Krispy Kreme does.

77
00:05:53,317 --> 00:05:59,468
You know, when you have your moment of sweet treat sharing, it's gotta be worth it, it's gotta be amazing.

78
00:05:59,468 --> 00:06:01,968
And that's why I think our donuts really, even in this changing world, are relevant.

